h3. Issue Summary
When creating a space template, users have the option to insert an Attachments macro into it. By doing so, saving the template and previewing it, an error message will be displayed saying the macro failed to load, due to missing permissions.


h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Navigate to Any space an access *Space Settings* > *Content Tools* > *Templates*
# Create a new Template;
# Insert an "Attachments" macro into it > Save the template;
# Now preview the template, by clicking its name (under 'User Created Templates');

h3. Expected Results
* Attachments macro to correctly be displayed under the template preview;

h3. Actual Results
* Users are shown the error 
{quote}
Error rendering macro 'attachments' : Could not check permissions for page: 0 v.1 no suitable delegate found.
{quote}

 !Screen Shot 2020-04-14 at 10.52.59.png|thumbnail! 

{panel:titleColor=#fff5e6|titleBGColor=#4da9ff|borderColor=#4d2800|borderStyle=dashed|bgColor=#e6f3ff}




(!) *NOTE*: This only affects the template's preview, and won't impact the created page based on it, or have any degradation on functionality whatsoever. The page would correctly display the macro, and receive attachments, both in draft and published mode.
{panel}
h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary
Pages with indented Action Items (tasks) fail to convert to the new editor

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a page (or template) using the old editor;
# Insert an Action Item and some text;
# Hit Enter and another tasks will be created; This time indent this action item by hitting TAB on your keyboard;
 # Save the page and go back into edit mode;
 !Screen Shot 2020-04-01 at 11.09.35.png|thumbnail! 
# A message on the bottom on the page will be displayed, to convert this page to the new editor;
# Click to *Preview page* in the new editor 
 !Screen Shot 2020-04-01 at 11.07.17.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Expected Results
* Page to be correctly converted to the new editor;

h3. Actual Results
* Page fails to be converted due to indentation on action items
 !Screen Shot 2020-04-01 at 11.08.54.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround
* Removing the indentation from these items solves this conversion issue;

h3. Issue Summary
Images inserted into an *expand macro* inside a table cell wil fail to render some of these images.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new page using the new editor;
 # Insert a table into the page > Inside one of its cells insert an *Expand Macro*;
# Populate this macro with 4 or more images;
# Publish the page;

h3. Expected Results
* Images to be correctly displayed when the page is published.
h3. Actual Results
* When you click the Expand macro just a few images will load, and some won't

h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
